descript.purpose: The purpose of this data set is to show the locations of the sanitary sewer manholes.

horizpa.horizpar: GPS technology was used to verify location of the water distribution, sanitary sewer and storm water drainage surface structures resulting in a consistent positional error of less than one foot for the features that were captured using this method. The GPS collection equipment consisted of a Trimble Zephyr external antenna and a Trimble ProXH receiver. For system structures that have been marked and are visible on the VBMP aerial photography, specifically for water and storm water structures. Additionally, georeferenced plan sheets were also used to create system structure locations. These features were captured using heads up digitizing techniques resulting in a horizontal positional error of +/- 5 feet. For other system structures that were unable to be located visibly were located via field survey books that indicated measured distances to locate the feature. Consult the field "LocationStatus" for the process step used to capture the system structure location.
